    <title>A Renormalizable and Unitary Approach to Quantum Gravity</title>
    <updated>2026-05-18T03:46:04Z</updated>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.17817v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2605.17817v1" rel="related" type="application/pdf" title="pdf"/>
    <summary>A Lagrange multiplier field restricts the quantum corrections to the Einstein-Hilbert action at one-loop order, yielding a model that is renormalizable and unitary while reproducing the Einstein field equations in the classical limit.</summary>
